title.narrative: PSE OP 3 - SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: Dialogue and partnerships with the Government and donors are established to develop a national social protection framework and to progressively integrate social protection measures into relevant programme areas., which contributes to Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Greater national commitment, accountability and capacity to legislate, plan and budget for inclusive social policies, and progressively integrate social protection measures into relevant programme areas.

description.narrative: In 2020, UNICEF continued to support;the;implementation of the;national social protection programmes;(FIAVOTA and LUL) and launched a new integrated programme;(FAGNAVOTSE).;UNICEF;led with the Government;the;Cash Working Group to coordinate;the;expansion of;cash transfers to respond to;the socio-economic impact of;COVID-19;(leveraging over USD;$15 million);and;more recently;the drought in the south. Over 770,000;children benefitted from the social protection in 2020, of which 30,700 through UNICEF financing.;Several studies have been initiated to;strengthen;social protection;and make it more child-sensitive, gender-responsive and disability-inclusive.;; | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
